The close of the sourteenth century also witnessed the emancipation of the Chancellor from the control ostheBishopofLincoln. The earliest Chancellors had been simply officers oi the Diocesan, set by him over the scholars, and is they were not actually nominated by him, required confirmation of their election at his hands.
